This paper is primarily focused on image inpainting, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of geometrical alignment, which could potentially fall under graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the experiments conducted on public datasets suggest that it could also be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
